# TheKeyMachine changelog
#
# Format:
# version:
#   - kind: short description
#
# Supported kinds: new, changed, polish, bugfix.
# Rule: keep each version to 6 changes at most.
# Rule: sort entries by main group in this order: New, Changed, Polish, Bugfix.
# Rule: keep descriptions short and efficient.
# Rule: focus on animation tool changes, visible workflow changes, and bugfixes.
# Rule: do not include repo housekeeping, docs, funding, metadata, or asset-only changes.
# Rule: avoid code technicalities such as modules, APIs, registries, packages, internal managers, or implementation refactors.
# Rule: rephrase technical changes into animator-facing behavior when there is a visible effect.

0.1.94:
  - new: Version history window from the About dialog
  - polish: Bug Report window spacing and field layout
  - polish: Sending bug reports keeps Maya responsive
  - polish: Disabled dialog buttons are easier to read
  - bugfix: Bug Report action opens the report window again
  - bugfix: Menu tooltips stay visible while hovering actions

